import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data = data.dropna(subset=['away_score'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='away_score', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['away_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['away_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['goal_difference'] = data['goal_difference'].astype(int)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='goal_difference', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['goal_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['goal_difference'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['goal_difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['goal_difference'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of goal differences?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['home_team', 'home_score']]
    data = data.groupby(['home_team']).mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['home_score'], ascending=False)
    ax = sns.barplot(x='home_team', y='home_score', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    ax.axhline(y=data['home_score'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['home_score'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['away_team'] = data['away_team'].astype('category')
    data['away_score'] = data['away_score'].astype('float')
    avg_away_scores = data.groupby('away_team')['away_score'].mean().reset_index()
    avg_away_scores = avg_away_scores.sort_values(by='away_score', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='away_team', y='away_score', data=avg_away_scores, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.axhline(y=avg_away_scores['away_score'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Average Away Score: {:.2f}'.format(avg_away_scores['away_score'].max()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Away Team')
    plt.ylabel('Average Away Score')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
